prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "yellow-graffiti-fisheye-manga-street-poster-style" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: Create a hybrid street poster with a cool fisheye urban-photo background, one oversized centered manga cutout subject in the foreground, a large top-band yellow spray-paint headline, short white caption hits near the middle, and a chalky white pavement tag or painted ground mark at the bottom. Keep the subject close to camera with top-down scale distortion, large head and hands, smaller feet, and street lines bending into the fisheye perspective.
- Typography: Use loose hand-sprayed yellow graffiti for the main headline, with rounded thick strokes, drips, dot overspray, and uneven baseline. Use compact white block captions as short street-zine callouts. Use chalky or spray-painted ground lettering for the bottom mark. Make all text graphic and brief, not clean corporate typography.
- Color: Keep the background mostly cool blue-gray, concrete gray, asphalt charcoal, vending-light white, and muted storefront color. Render the subject in warmer cream, tan, peach, muted browns, and black or dark brown ink. Use electric yellow as the loud accent and white as secondary caption paint.
- Texture and lighting: Use realistic asphalt grain, storefront reflections, compressed street-photo detail, smooth manga ink contours, simple cell shading, blush hatch marks, spray-paint speckle, rough pavement paint, and flat overcast daylight with subtle machine glow. Avoid cinematic shadows, glossy 3D depth, and heavy blur.
- Graphic elements: Add yellow overspray dots, small sticker-like marks, white caption hits, curb stripes, road paint, vending or storefront glow, concrete seams, and a bottom pavement tag that follows perspective.

Avoid: photoreal-only portraits, pure anime backgrounds, 3D render, glossy vector poster, clean corporate layout, dense tabloid collage panels, luxury minimalism, heavy gradients, bokeh blur, real brand logos, watermarks, usernames, QR codes, platform marks, creator signatures, exact source text, copied character, copied pose, copied vending-machine composition, and any source-specific franchise identity.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text, while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
